## 3. Smart Water Bottle Reminder

**What it does:** This health-focused device reminds students to drink water at regular intervals (every 30-60 minutes). It uses an RTC (Real-Time Clock) module to keep accurate time and triggers a buzzer and LED at set intervals. Students can press a button to acknowledge they've had water, which resets the timer. An optional LCD can display the time and reminder messages.

**Real-world applications:**

- Health monitoring devices
- Medication reminder systems
- Timer-based automation
- Fitness trackers

**Learning outcomes:**

- Time-based programming
- RTC module usage
- Creating reminder systems
- Health and wellness awareness

**Difficulty Level:** Intermediate 
**Recommended for:** Classes 6-8 
**Project Duration:** 2-3 hours

