## 5. Traffic Light Simulator

**What it does:** This project simulates a real traffic signal with three LEDs (red, yellow, green) that light up in sequence with proper timing. Red stays on longest, then yellow briefly, then green. An optional pedestrian crossing button can be added to change the sequence.

**Real-world applications:**

- Actual traffic management systems
- Railway crossing signals
- Industrial process indicators
- Sequential control systems

**Learning outcomes:**

- Timing and delays in programming
- Sequential logic
- Loop concepts
- Real-world system modeling

**Difficulty Level:** Beginner 
**Recommended for:** Classes 5-6 
**Project Duration:** 45 minutes - 1 hour

